pt locations. If this data may be exported or inspected outside the local machine, prefer omitting `source-path` or storing a hash/basename, and avoid duplicating raw `cwd` into the envelope/scalars.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=154 end=158 priority=2 confidence=0.86}\\n\\n**Equilibrium**\\n\\nMostly reached on algorithm complexity: `/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/redaction.rs` is compact, value-only, and appropriately best-effort for a POC. I would not turn it into a scanner framework. The remaining imbalance is storage consistency: redacted transcript content is careful, but metadata/key storage still leaks the identifiers/paths above.\\n\\nValidation: `cargo test -p but-agentlog redaction --no-fail-fast` passed.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>"}]}}}